  "prompt": "Does India contribute to the ISS (International Space Station)?",
  "response": "As of October **2023**, India does not directly contribute to the **International Space Station (ISS)**. The ISS is a collaborative project involving **NASA** (United States), **Roscosmos** (Russia), **ESA** (European Space Agency), **JAXA** (Japan), and **CSA** (Canada). While India has a burgeoning space program led by the **Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO)**, it has not been a formal partner in the ISS project.\n\nHowever, India has expressed interest in collaborating with international partners in space exploration. For instance:\n- ISRO has worked with NASA and other space agencies on satellite launches and joint missions.\n- India\u2019s **Gaganyaan** program, aimed at sending Indian astronauts to space, could pave the way for future collaboration with the ISS or similar projects.\n- ISRO has also discussed the possibility of building its own **space station** in the future.\n\nWhile India is not currently involved in the ISS, its growing capabilities in space technology and exploration suggest potential for future collaboration in international space initiatives.",
